main event: An unidentified flying object was reported over Pensacola, Florida on 3 September 1960, with a duration of observation lasting three minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, white, round object exhibiting high-speed maneuvers., The sighting was made at 2300Z and lasted for approximately three minutes., The object was reported to be at a very high altitude and moving quickly., The case is considered unidentified, with a possibility that it could have been a weather balloon., A military duty officer also observed a cylindrical object with red and blue lights moving rapidly on 7 September 1960.
witness description: Duty officer, Weather Observation Section, NAS Pensacola
